    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - TRANSFER CASES - ASSEMBLE - INTERMEDIATE SHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="10">
        <title>INTERMEDIATE SHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1303449">Figure 49</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1303449" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303449.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 49. Intermediate Shaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position housing with three holes up.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install bearing into center bore of housing
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303450">(Figure 50)</hotlnk>. Make sure bearing is seated in bearing bore.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303450" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303450.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 50. Install Bearing Into Center Bore of Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place lower output gear, HUB UP, into housing and slide to small bore
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303451">(Figure 51)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303451" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303451.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 51. Install Lower Output Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place intermediate gear, HUB DOWN, into housing and slide to center of housing
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303452">(Figure 52)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303452" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303452.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. Install Intermediate Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place upper input gear into housing, HUB UP
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303453">(Figure 53)</hotlnk>
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303453" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303453.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 53. Install Upper Input Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a driver and soft hammer to install intermediate shaft with threaded hole up
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303454">(Figure 54)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303454" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303454.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 54. Install Intermediate Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install spacer onto intermediate shaft
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303455">(Figure 55)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303455" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303455.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Install Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a driver and soft hammer to install bearing onto intermediate shaft and into housing
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303456">(Figure 56)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303456" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303456.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 56. Install Bearing Onto Intermediate Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If unit has oil pump, install one .254 mm (.010 inch) shim and one 1.27 mm (.050 inch) shim
                and drivescrew
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303457">(Figure 57)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303457" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303457.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 57. Install Shims And Drivescrew</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten drivescrew to 102 to 122 Nm (75 to 90 ft-lbs),
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303458">(Figure 58)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303458" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303458.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 58. Tighten Drivescrew</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
